# Delivery workflow (always follow)

Every task—planning, review, fix, test, or implementation—must follow this sequence. Do not skip steps unless the user explicitly asks for docs-only or question-only work.

## 1. Plan

- Restate the goal, acceptance criteria, and affected layers (UI, domain, data, CI, QA).
- Read existing code and conventions before designing; prefer extending over inventing.
- Call out risks (i18n, persistence, keyboard/scroll, AI read-only vs editable data, platform splits).
- Keep scope minimal: smallest correct change.

## 2. Implement

- Match project architecture and naming; reuse shared components (`ScreenLayout`, `FamilyLogistics*`, scaffolds).
- No drive-by refactors, secrets in repo, or hardcoded user-facing strings (see `i18n-multilingual.mdc`).
- Platform code only when no multiplatform library exists (`expect`/`actual` as last resort).

## 3. Test

- **Unit** (`commonTest`): domain logic, screen models, repositories, codecs, i18n key parity.
- **Instrumented** (`androidInstrumentedTest`): critical UX paths with `testTag`s; use fakes, not production network.
- Update `firebase-appdistribution-testcases.yaml` when user-facing flows change.
- Run relevant Gradle tasks before claiming done (e.g. `:composeApp:testDebugUnitTest`).

## 4. Review (self-check)

- UX: loading/error/empty states, snackbars, keyboard + `imePadding`, accessibility labels on icons.
- Architecture: dependencies point inward; no UI in domain/data.
- Security: no credentials committed; env/secrets only in CI secrets.
- i18n: follow `i18n-multilingual.mdc` (all 8 locales, no hardcoded UI copy, parity tests green).

## 5. CI/CD alignment

- Push should pass unit tests; instrumented tests via `workflow_dispatch` → `android-instrumented-tests`.
- Firebase releases: keep `firebase-appdistribution-testcases.yaml` in sync; release notes reference QA checklist when distributing.

## Definition of done

Feature works on target platforms, tests added/updated and passing, strings localized, manual QA steps documented, no new linter issues in touched files.
